channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Famed economist Ed Yardeni predicts it’ll be ‘one and done’ for Fed rate cuts despite Wall Street expectations
item.description: Yardeni is unconvinced the data is cool enough to push Chair Powell and his colleagues to multiple cuts: "It'll be dovish but not as dovish as the market is discounting."

item.title: Macy’s cuts sales forecast as department stores struggle to draw shoppers
item.description: Macy's beat quarterly earnings expectations but it cut its sales forecast for the full year.

item.title: U.K. ends app store probes into Google and Apple but says it'll use new powers
France to donate 100,000 mpox vaccines as nation prepares for outbreak at home
item.description: Last week the health agency of the African Union said 200,000 vaccines would be deployed across Africa, due to agreements with the EU and Danish drug company Bavarian Nordic.

item.title: After mini-boom, weekly mortgage refinance demand falls back 15%. Here's why.
item.description: Applications to refinance a home loan dropped 15% from the previous week, according to the Mortgage Bankers Association's seasonally adjusted index.

item.title: Target stock jumps as discounter beats estimates and lifts guidance
Las Vegas Venetian workers win historic contract with major pay boosts
item.description: Described by the Culinary Union as their “best contracts ever,” the deals ended lengthy labor disputes that had brought the threat of a historic strike to the Las Vegas Strip.

item.title: 'Pick a number': Strategist says the U.S. dollar will drift much lower against the Japanese yen
item.description: The U.S. dollar is likely to continue to drift lower against the Japanese yen over the coming months, according to one market strategist.

item.title: Walmart has entirely sold out of its stake in China's JD.com
Atlassian’s billionaire cofounder wants to send renewable power from Australia to Singapore via a 2,600 mile-long undersea cable
item.description: On Wednesday, Australia approved an ambitious project from Mike Cannon-Brookes's SunCable to connect Singapore with a massive Australian solar farm.

item.title: China calls EU tariffs on EVs unfair, says it will take necessary measures to defend industry
item.description: Beijing said it continues to believe the EU's probe into China's subsidies for EVs are promoting unfair competition in the name of fair competition.

item.title: S&P 500 bursts back with most sharp daily gains in any month since June 2023
Tesla is the EU’s top choice getting lower tariffs compared to rivals on its China-made cars
item.description: The European Union said Tuesday it plans to introduce an additional 9% tariff on Teslas imported from China.

item.title: Health-care system Sesame to offer compounded versions of Wegovy through new $249 weight loss program
item.description: Sesame is offering compounded semaglutide — the active ingredient in Wegovy and Ozempic — to help users access obesity and diabetes treatments amid shortages.

item.title: How several people in missing tycoon Mike Lynch’s fraud trial have met tragedy
